    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.7.2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nRed Hat Enterprise Linux 7.7\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGNOME Terminal 3.28.2 using VTE 0.52.2 +GNUTLS\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nscreen-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nappimage\n\n### How to reproduce the issue\n\nnvim --clean\r\n\r\n:lua vim.opt_local.efm = vim.opt_global.efm:get()\r\n:lua vim.opt_local.efm = vim.o.efm\r\n:lua vim.bo.efm = vim.o.efm\r\n:lua vim.bo.efm = table.concat(vim.opt_global.efm:get(), ',')\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nCopy the exact value of the global efm to the local option\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nThe first 2 options truncate the original value and sets an invalid string into the local efm",
